### Mitsubishi MELCloud login
POST https://app.melcloud.com/Mitsubishi.Wifi.Client/Login/ClientLogin
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/javascript, */*; q=0.01
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest
Cookie: policyaccepted=true
User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (X11; Linux x86_64; rv:73.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/73.0

{
  "Email": "{{mitsubishi_ac_username}}",
  "Password": "{{mitsubishi_ac_password}}",
  "Language": 0,
  "AppVersion": "1.38.0.1",
  "Persist": true,
  "CaptchaResponse": null
}


### Get all MELCloud devices
### Check response manually and pick your AC unit DeviceID and BuildingID.
GET https://app.melcloud.com/Mitsubishi.Wifi.Client/User/ListDevices
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/javascript, */*; q=0.01
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest
Cookie: policyaccepted=true
User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (X11; Linux x86_64; rv:73.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/73.0
X-MitsContextKey: {{mitsubishi_ac_context_key}}


### Get AC state
GET https://app.melcloud.com/Mitsubishi.Wifi.Client/Device/Get?id={{mitsubishi_ac_device_id}}&
    buildingID={{mitsubishi_ac_building_id}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/javascript, */*; q=0.01
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest
Cookie: policyaccepted=true
User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (X11; Linux x86_64; rv:73.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/73.0
X-MitsContextKey: {{mitsubishi_ac_context_key}}


### Get AC unit details
POST https://app.melcloud.com/Mitsubishi.Wifi.Client/Device/ListDeviceUnits
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/javascript, */*; q=0.01
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest
Cookie: policyaccepted=true
User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (X11; Linux x86_64; rv:73.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/73.0
X-MitsContextKey: {{mitsubishi_ac_context_key}}

{
  "deviceId": {{mitsubishi_ac_device_id}}
}


### Set AC state
### Study flow:
### 1. Call "Get AC state"
### 2. Copy full JSON response here
### 3. Modify only needed fields
### 4. Set matching EffectiveFlags
###
### Useful fields for air-to-air units:
### - Power: true / false
### - OperationMode: 1=heat, 2=dry, 3=cool, 7=fan_only, 8=auto
### - SetTemperature: target temperature
### - SetFanSpeed: 0=auto, 1..N=speeds
### - VaneVertical: 0=auto, 1..5=fixed, 7=swing
### - VaneHorizontal: 0=auto, 1..5=fixed, 8=split, 12=swing
###
### EffectiveFlags bits:
### - 0x01 power
### - 0x02 mode
### - 0x04 temperature
### - 0x08 fan speed
### - 0x10 vertical vane
### - 0x100 horizontal vane
POST https://app.melcloud.com/Mitsubishi.Wifi.Client/Device/SetAta
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/javascript, */*; q=0.01
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest
Cookie: policyaccepted=true
User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (X11; Linux x86_64; rv:73.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/73.0
X-MitsContextKey: {{mitsubishi_ac_context_key}}

{
  "DeviceID": {{mitsubishi_ac_device_id}},
  "BuildingID": {{mitsubishi_ac_building_id}},
  "Power": true,
  "OperationMode": 3,
  "SetTemperature": 21.0,
  "SetFanSpeed": 0,
  "VaneVertical": 0,
  "VaneHorizontal": 0,
  "EffectiveFlags": 15,
  "HasPendingCommand": true
}


### Example: turn AC off
### In real use, copy full state from "Get AC state" and only change fields you want.
POST https://app.melcloud.com/Mitsubishi.Wifi.Client/Device/SetAta
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/javascript, */*; q=0.01
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest
Cookie: policyaccepted=true
User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (X11; Linux x86_64; rv:73.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/73.0
X-MitsContextKey: {{mitsubishi_ac_context_key}}

{
  "DeviceID": {{mitsubishi_ac_device_id}},
  "BuildingID": {{mitsubishi_ac_building_id}},
  "Power": false,
  "EffectiveFlags": 1,
  "HasPendingCommand": true
}
